# context & summary
projectDescription: |
  <em>project: kilter</em> is a 15-week solo design project for a UMD course, where I focused on my personal passion for weightlifting. 
  I designed a modular spreadsheet application to give seasoned lifters the streamlined control missing from traditional training tools. 
  The product centers on a plugin system and an intuitive interface that lets lifters customize their workflow to train more efficiently. 
  The scope was limited to interface design without coding requirements. Final deliverables included 12-14 polished Figma screens or a 
  project equal in effort.

